                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12697044" author="gillouxgaillard@wanadoo.fr" created="Wed, 8 Apr 2009 14:44:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached unit test showing the issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12697098" author="gillouxgaillard@wanadoo.fr" created="Wed, 8 Apr 2009 16:57:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The reason why &lt;tt&gt;sendNoOp&lt;/tt&gt; returns false is that &lt;tt&gt;completePendingCommand&lt;/tt&gt; was not called because of the socket exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The consequence is that any further usages of the FTPClient instance lead to inconsistent server message. At call &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt;, the client reads the server response for the call &lt;em&gt;n - 1&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13001685" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2011 21:45:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by calling Util.closeQuietly(socket); instead of socket.close() in private FTPListParseEngine initiateListParsing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
